<p>[Letter from Maurice Alfred Fergusson]<br/>France<br/>7.4.18</p>
<p>Dear Mrs Garling<br/>Fergusson is my name, poor old Terry and I were the best of pals and fellow officers for a long time; so I am writing to you to give you my deepest sympathy.<br/>Terry was a son to be proud of, I can't say enough for him, he was just about the bravest man I have ever known and the 'whitest'.  His men loved him, his officers too.  He was always where the trouble was, in the shape of shelling, I mean.  He was hit whilst walking up and down his</p>
